#: ../../S/Share-and-enjoy-.rst:5
msgid "Share and enjoy!"
msgstr "Share and enjoy!"

#: ../../S/Share-and-enjoy-.rst:7
msgid "imp\\."
msgstr "imp\\."

#: ../../S/Share-and-enjoy-.rst:10
msgid ""
"Commonly found at the end of software release announcements and "
":ref:`README-file`\\s, this phrase indicates allegiance to the hacker ethic "
"of free information sharing (see :ref:`hacker-ethic`\\, sense 1)."
msgstr ""
"ソフトウェアのリリース告知や\\ :ref:`README-file`\\ "
"の末尾によく見られるこのフレーズは、自由な情報共有というハッカー倫理への忠誠を示す(\\ :ref:`hacker-ethic`\\ 、語義1を参照)。"

#: ../../S/Share-and-enjoy-.rst:13
msgid ""
"The motto of the complaints division of Sirius Cybernetics Corporation (the "
"ultimate gaggle of incompetent :ref:`suit`\\s) in Douglas Adams's *Hitch "
"Hiker's Guide to the Galaxy*\\. The irony of using this as a cultural "
"recognition signal appeals to hackers."
msgstr ""
"Douglas Adamsの\\ *Hitch Hiker's Guide to the Galaxy*\\ における、Sirius "
"Cybernetics Corporation(無能な\\ :ref:`suit`\\ "
"たちの究極の集団)の苦情処理部門の標語。これを文化的な認識の合図として使う皮肉が、ハッカーの心に訴える。"
